1. PATH TRAVERSAL
Path Traversal occurs when an application exposes backend file system paths through user input.

LAB 1: FILE PATH TRAVERSAL SIMPLE CASE
CWE ID: 22 (Improper Limitation of a Pathname to a Restricted Directory) 
CVSS score - 7.3 (High)

Description: path traversal vulnerability in the display of product images.

Impact: the ability to bypass access controls and read arbitrary files on the server.

POC (Proof of concept):
intercept the request with parameter file name.
modify file name to ../../../etc/passwd.
server responded with the requested file.

Screenshot: https://0ac90033041a64178154eeee00ab00ea.web-security-academy.net/product?productId=1
Congratulations, you solved the lab!

Prevention: 
Serve Files by ID
Validate Input Against an Allowlist- whitelisting
Validate the Resolved Path
Restrict File System Permissions
Avoid passing user input to filesystem APIs



